Lucan. lib. 1. — Nullos habitura triumphos? Where one Member wounds another to the hazard of the whole Body? that ſo we might avenge the bloud of Gods Servants,Revel. 19.2. which hath ſo long time called, cried for revenge; and ſet a bound to
Turks pride, and propagate the glorious Goſpel of our Saviour. While now our diſcord is his advantage, and our Wars his opportunity.
